		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">loopy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Try to find as small a ZIF socket as you can, there's not much room on these NES boards.  You'd have a hard time making that big green monster fit.</div>
<br />
<br />I couldn't find this image earlier, but here is (bad) top-down picture of the ZIF sockets I use. As Loopy said, there isn't much room in there.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://www.srvperformance.com/images/zif.jpg" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />It's called a low profile ZIF socket. It's about half the height, and not as wide, either. I found them cheap on eBay, because people use them in some types of Honda's.
<br />
<br />NC

		

